texts: The advocacy tent is the symbol of unity for local employees who have sacrificed and dedicated years of service for German forces in North of Afghanistan. Exact...ly, one year has passed with few and little achievements of peaceful demonstration, gathering, tenting for justice over a year. We once more thanks international  medias which broadcasted our activity and sent our voice to respect German authorities and institutions that are emphasizing on humanitarian protection to facilitate relocation of Hundokosh employees left behind and ignored, but it is not significant enough ,cause, German Military is still silent and does nothing to save the life of its employees. On 31 Aug 2019 was the anniversary of our justice claiming process so, we renewed our banners and the tent to show them that we will never withdraw from our claims. Years of experience, and performing duty alongside German forces cost us so expensive that will be compensated by our death. Security situation is worsening than any other times and threat circle trapped us not only in Mazar-e-Sharif , but in its neighboring provinces, by standing under the flag of Germany and tenting in front of German Military base made us even bad faces on areas where we live and everyday receive threat messages. Our message is clear to German Military that an immediate measure should be taken as we did this by sending three letters to General Brotz Office mentioning our concerns, including a memorial stone to show our dignity and value to German mission in Afghanistan and we still count ourselves as German Military partners who left behind.

Last night i was on a tour around the art week and tried to catch this (in)famous group performing in ruins of a closter in the city center. The line was long, we were late, so we watched it from afar - few minutes later, there was a sound of an explosion, screams and people running. It turned out the performers set some of the audience members on fire by accident. I love Berlin's punk, wild, adventurous spirit and I love the space for risk it creates, but damn, how can any group, especially an established one, allow for such an amateur, terrible mistake to happen? And then take down the FB event and the instagram page to silence the people who might want to talk about it, or maybe find each other. Great work, artists.
